{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSHostingController\/sizingOptions","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sizingOptions"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSHostingSizingOptions","preciseIdentifier":"s:11OpenSwiftUI22NSHostingSizingOptionsV","text":"NSHostingSizingOptions"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"NSHostingController can create minimum, maximum, and ideal (content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"size) constraints that are derived from its SwiftUI view content. These"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constraints are only created when Auto Layout constraints are otherwise"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"being used in the containing window."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the NSHostingController is set as the ","type":"text"},{"code":"contentViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSWindow","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", it will also update the window’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"contentMinSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"contentMaxSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" based on the minimum and maximum size of its SwiftUI","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"tex